I upgraded the Boostrap Sass to 3.3.4.1 from 3.3.3, using Compass 1.1.0.alpha.3 in Win8/Pro

Because I need to use a relative path for the Boostrap Sass, I try to find the solution.
And I come up with #650 
I then added @import "bootstrap-sprockets";
hopefully to make it work, but it didn't, then I meet the problem with output like:

when I use the default settings with
@import "bootstrap-compass";
@import "bootstrap-sprockets";
@import "bootstrap";

the @font-face will output with `url(font-url("path string"))...`

I found someone output the thing with `url(url(...`
then I try to find out the reason.

in bootstrap-sass-3.3.4.1\assets\stylesheets\_bootstrap-sprockets.scss
It is using something like
`@function twbs-font-path($path) {
  @return font-path($path);
}

@function twbs-image-path($path) {
  @return image-path($path);
}`

but font-path seems not exist in Compass (at least not in 1.1.0.alpha.3), so I suspect it means to use the function font-url() instead, if I just change the function
from `@return font-path($path);` to `@return font-url($path);`
it output the result as #667 

So I then add true after the $path parameter to make it output path only,
according to [compass DOC](http://compass-style.org/reference/compass/helpers/urls/)
